# Realtime / Socket.IO Rules

## Gateway responsibility — only 3 things
1. Handle the socket event
2. Call a service method for any logic
3. Emit the result to the correct room

The gateway is a thin transport layer. It has no business logic.

## Room naming convention
```
channel:{channelId}    ← message broadcast room
server:{serverId}      ← server-level events (e.g. new channel created)
```

## Connection lifecycle
```typescript
handleConnection(client: Socket) {
  // Authenticate JWT from handshake.auth.token
  // Attach userId to client.data.userId
  // Do NOT join rooms here — wait for explicit join event
}

handleDisconnect(client: Socket) {
  // No cleanup needed for rooms — Socket.IO handles it
}
```

## Join channel room — explicit event required
Client must emit `join_channel` with `{ channelId }`.
Gateway checks membership (via service), then adds to room.

```typescript
@SubscribeMessage('join_channel')
async handleJoinChannel(client: Socket, { channelId }: { channelId: string }) {
  await this.channelService.assertMembership(client.data.userId, channelId);
  client.join(`channel:${channelId}`);
}
```

## Send message event
```typescript
@SubscribeMessage('send_message')
async handleSendMessage(client: Socket, dto: SendMessageDto) {
  const msg = await this.messageService.sendMessage({
    ...dto,
    userId: client.data.userId,   // always from socket auth, never from client payload
  });
  this.server.to(`channel:${dto.channelId}`).emit('new_message', msg);
}
```

## Security: never trust client-sent userId
`userId` on every event MUST come from `client.data.userId` (set during JWT auth at connection).
If the client sends a `userId` field in the payload, ignore it.

## Error handling in gateway
```typescript
// Emit error back to the requesting client only, don't crash the server
try {
  ...
} catch (err) {
  client.emit('error', { message: err.message });
}
```

## What does NOT belong in the gateway
- DB queries (call service instead)
- Permission logic (call service instead)
- Any `if` condition about domain rules
- Message formatting or transformation
